<table class="text text--article text--padding-vertical" width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="table-layout: fixed;"> <tbody><tr> <td class="text_content-cell content-padding-horizontal" style="text-align: left; font-family: Tahoma,Geneva,sans-serif; color: #36495F; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.2; display: block; word-wrap: break-word; padding: 10px 20px;" align="left" valign="top">
<p style="text-align: center; margin: 0;" align="center"><span style="font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-weight: bold;">2023 Lenten Study Series has been re-scheduled to </span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin: 0;" align="center"><span style="font-size: 18px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-weight: bold;">Thursday ﻿March 23 &amp; March 30</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0;"><br></p>
<p style="margin: 0;"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The season of Lent is an opportunity for spiritual growth and development. </span><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Lenten study group met on Thursday, March 16 to share a delicious and varied </span><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: italic;">soup &amp; bread</span><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> meal, then enjoyed lively discussion of selected readings from the memoir titled, </span><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">My Struggle to Be Human</span><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> by theologian and peace activist, Walter Wink. A different selection of readings is planned for each session. Our discussion will reflect on our own lives and efforts to grow in faith and concern for other people. Study materials will be provided each week. For more information contact a deacon (Jean Copelin or Sarah Seamans) or Pastor Chris.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin: 0;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Please join us to continue this Lenten Study on Thursday, March 23, and 30. We gather first for a simple meal of soup and bread at 6:00 pm followed by study group discussion at 7:00 pm.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin: 0;" align="left"><br></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin: 0;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Grace &amp; Peace</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin: 0;" align="left"><br></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin: 0;" align="left"><span style="font-size: 18px; font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Chris</span></p>
